pageTitle: Chris Soules and Robert Herjavec Double Elimination on DWTS: Week 8 Results | Dancing With The Stars - ABC.com
textBeforeTable: WEEK 8 SCORES:   Chris Soules & Witney Carson Eliminated This Week: Robert Herjavec & Kym Johnson Lowest Score: Robert Herjavec & Kym Johnson - 62 points (Contemporary 33 pts., Samba 29 pts.) Top Score: Rumer Willis & Valentin Chmerkovskiy - 80 points (Rumba 40 pts., Paso Doble 40 pts.) It was all up to the fans as Dancing with the Stars season 20 celebrated America's Choice Night as each of the six remaining couples had to use a song and dance style chosen by fans on Twitter. Then, everyone had to pick an eliminated pro or member of the dance troupe to team up with for a Trio Dance. While the added pressure brought out the best in some of the competitiors, others crumbled and at the end of the night it was not one, but two couples that were eliminated. Once again, our hosts Tom Bergeron and Erin Andrews welcomed us back to the ballroom and judges Carrie Ann Inaba, Len Goodman, Julianne Hough and Bruno Tonioli were on-hand to critique the performances. And by the end of the Week 8 Results show, it was time to say goodbye to Bachelor Chris Soules and Shark Tank's Robert Herjavec.
